I&#x27;m a zsh-er and use oh-my-zsh, but I borrowed the syntax highlighting, called it `sat` short for &quot;source cat&quot;, and piped through less for paginated output:<p><pre><code>  # before use: [sudo] easy_install pygments
  alias sat=&#x27;pygmentize -O style=monokai -f console256 -g | less&#x27;
</code></pre>
I like these kinds of projects, because someone always shows me something in my set up I don&#x27;t have, and it&#x27;s really trivial to borrow from them.<p>In return, I feel everyone should have a proper git log alias, here&#x27;s mine:<p><pre><code>  alias logg=&quot;git log --graph --oneline --all --decorate --abbrev-commit&quot;
</code></pre>
Example output: <a href=\http://d.pr/i/B9LT" rel="nofollow">http://d.pr/i/B9LT</a>"
